 executed from /src\n# From /src, PROJ directory exists (mounted volume at /src/PROJ)\n# Change to PROJ directory to find curl and libtiff subdirectories\nif [ -d \"PROJ\" ]; then\n    cd PROJ\nelse\n    echo \"ERROR: PROJ directory not found. Current directory: $(pwd)\"\n    echo \"Directory contents:\"\n    ls -la\n    exit 1\nfi\n\n# build libcurl.a (building against Ubuntu libcurl.a doesn't work easily)\ncd curl\n---=== FILE ===---\n/root/fix_build_agent/process/project/proj4/test/fuzzers/build.sh\n---=== ORIGINAL ===---\n# build libtiff.a\ncd libtiff\n./autogen.sh\n./configure --disable-shared --prefix=$SRC/install\nmake -j$(nproc)\nmake install\ncd ..\n\nmkdir build\ncd build\n---=== REPLACEMENT ===---\n# build libtiff.a\ncd libtiff\n./autogen.sh\n./configure --disable-shared --prefix=$SRC/install\nmake -j$(nproc)\nmake install\ncd ..\n\nmkdir build\ncd build"})
