 doesn't strictly require OpenSSL.\n5. **Dockerfile-Centric Fix**: Make all environment changes in the Dockerfile where they will be baked into the image, avoiding runtime script issues.\n\n**Specific Observations:**\n1. The curl configure script is hardcoded to check for OpenSSL >= v3 and fails when it finds 1.1.1\n2. pkg-config is finding system OpenSSL despite our attempts to override it\n3. Docker caching may be preventing our script changes from taking effect\n4. The `apt-get install` command is installing libssl-dev before our removal attempts can work\n5. Environment variables set in build.sh may not override hardcoded pkg-config paths\n\n**Recommended Approach for Strategy B:**\n1. **Prevent System OpenSSL Installation**: Modify the Dockerfile to NOT install libssl-dev at all\n2. **Early OpenSSL Build**: Build OpenSSL 3.x early in the Dockerfile, before any other dependencies\n3. **Environment Setup in Dockerfile**: Set up PKG_CONFIG_PATH, LD_LIBRARY_PATH, etc. in the Dockerfile itself, not just in build.sh\n4. **Complete Path Isolation**: Install OpenSSL 3.x to a non-standard location and ensure all paths point only to that location\n5. **Verify Before Build**: Add verification steps to ensure the correct OpenSSL is being used before attempting to build curl\n6. **Consider SSL Alternatives**: Check if curl can be built with --without-ssl or with --with-wolfssl/--with-gnutls if OpenSSL 3.x proves too difficult\n\n**Critical Insight from Rollback:**\n- Strategy A (patching config files) failed due to execution order and Docker caching issues\n- Need a more fundamental approach that sets up the environment correctly from the start\n- The Dockerfile is the right place to fix environment issues, not just build.sh\n- System package installation happens before our build.sh script runs, making removal attempts ineffective\n\n**Implementation Plan:**\n1. Modify Dockerfile to skip libssl-dev installation\n2. Build OpenSSL 3.x with custom prefix early in Dockerfile\n3. Set environment variables globally in Dockerfile\n4. Update build.sh to rely on these pre-configured environment settings\n5. Add verification steps to confirm OpenSSL 3.x is being used"})
